<br />
Again, the idea behind Keynes is that you borrow and spend money during the recession to get out of the recession more quickly. Then during the expansion, you cut the spending and pay back the debt.  The faster you can get your tax base growing, the faster you can start paying it back, rather than limping along for years.<br />
<br />
Problem with governments is once they start spending on something, they never want to pay it back.  Add in the fact that citizens nearly always start demanding tax cuts during any surplus and you see why politics and good economics rarely mix.<br />
<br />
We went into this recession with a lot of debt; that&#39;s the problem here, not the stimulus money that was spent during the recession. Ideally, we should have money saved for the inevitable recession that always comes.<br />
<br />
